arts.ttl: Shelbourne held to scoreless draw at home to Drogheda United
arts.sum: Douglas James Taylor tested Healy early in the second half as he was able to turn and scuff a shot goalward, but his effort was saved by the Shels netminder who pushed it out for a corner. However, it was Shels who had a massive to chance to net the opener of the game moments later as Harry Wood caught a terrific delivery from Tyreke Wilson on the volley that left Luke Dennison static in the Drogheda goal but ultimately only narrowly crept wide.
